commit.message:
PyPI now supports markdown long_description -- use it

Instead of converting README.md to rst, simply use the markdown version.
setuptools and PyPI now support it as native format.

For full details, see:

https://dustingram.com/articles/2018/03/16/markdown-descriptions-on-pypi/

Use flake8 to apply static analysis to the project

Found and fixed all warnings and errors including unused imports and
variables as well as comparing booleans with '==' instead of 'is'.
Should help the project in line with community standards going forward.

Enable pip cache in Travis CI

Reduce load on PyPI servers and slightly speed up builds.

For more information, see:

https://docs.travis-ci.com/user/caching/#pip-cache

Replace datetime use with a monotonic clock

A monotonic clock is one never goes backwards. It does not rely on the
system's date & time settings. It is most useful as a relative time for
calculating time deltas, not as an absolute time. Use this instead of
the datetime module for calculating elapsed times. In Python, this
feature is accessed through the time.monotonic() interface. This feature
is new to Python 3 so for Python 2.7, fallback to time.time().

https://docs.python.org/3/library/time.html#time.monotonic

> time.monotonic() → float
>
> Return the value (in fractional seconds) of a monotonic clock, i.e. a
> clock that cannot go backwards. The clock is not affected by system
> clock updates. The reference point of the returned value is undefined,
> so that only the difference between the results of consecutive calls
> is valid.
Drop unused 'six' dependency from tox.ini

Use 'dist: xenial' in Travis to add Python 3.7 testing

Travis officially added support for Xenial (with Python 3.7) on
2018-11-08.

https://blog.travis-ci.com/2018-11-08-xenial-release

Update all pypi.python.org URLs to pypi.org

For details on the new PyPI, see the blog post:

https://pythoninsider.blogspot.ca/2018/04/new-pypi-launched-legacy-pypi-shutting.html

Trim trailing white space throughout the project

Many editors clean up trailing white space on save. By removing it all
in one go, it helps keep future diffs cleaner by avoiding spurious white
space changes on unrelated lines.

Pass python_requires argument to setuptools

Helps pip decide what version of the library to install.

https://packaging.python.org/guides/distributing-packages-using-setuptools/#python-requires

> If your project only runs on certain Python versions, setting the
> python_requires argument to the appropriate PEP 440 version specifier
> string will prevent pip from installing the project on other Python
> versions.

https://setuptools.readthedocs.io/en/latest/setuptools.html#new-and-changed-setup-keywords

> python_requires
>
> A string corresponding to a version specifier (as defined in PEP 440)
> for the Python version, used to specify the Requires-Python defined in
> PEP 345.

Distribute package as a universal wheel

The package is pure Python. A single universal wheel can be created for
both Python2 and Python3.

https://pythonwheels.com/

Update trove classifiers for supported Python versions

EOL Pythons were removed in ad4cbb93ab8c680add78d650bf0c6cd9d3850c05.
